        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 1:49AM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 147 AM CDT, strong thunderstorms were developing along a line
extending from 5 miles east of Braddock to 8 miles northwest of
Linton to 9 miles northeast of Mcintosh, SD. Movement was northeast
at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Linton, Napoleon, Strasburg, Hazelton, Fort Yates, Selfridge, Solen,
Westfield, Cannon Ball, Braddock, Prairie Knights Resort, Temvik,
Breien, Kintyre, Huff, Fort Rice, Porcupine, and Standing Rock.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 300 AM CDT for
south central and southeastern North Dakota.</instruction>
